This script is to automatically restore a site from supplied backup files.

Extract this into the main Moodle directory (e.g. /var/www/html/moodle)

Ensure backup Moodledata is called 'moodledata.tar.gz'
Ensure backup database is called 'dump.sql'.

Run the `reset_moodle.php` file via cron or directly with `php reset_moodle.php`

If required, you can specify the location of the moodledata and database files:
`--moodledata=/path/of/moodledata.tar.gz`
`--database=/path/of/database.sql`

---

This script can also take a current backup of the Moodle site in preperation for automatic resets, using the `--backup` flag

`php reset_moodle.php --backup'
